				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Casual gamers have waited long enough.  If you guys think 2000 LDON points is easily attainable for a casual gamer, do you think they'd be casual?  
<br />

<br />
A casual gamer only dedicates on average 2 hours a day, less than 10 hours a week.  How many LDON's can they crank in that time span?
<br />

<br />
On my hot streaks, I could bring in 1000 points in one week.  But on my normally casual self, I'd consider myself lucky if I get 150 LDON points in one week.  And VT gear is not totally obsolete.  There are still a ton of INT casters out there that are level 65, dreaming of 3k HP's and +200 on all resists with FT 15.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
