				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">To me, it's not so much about gear as it is about content. I can only play about two hours a day. I usually do an LDON with a regular group, but I'm starting to find the game *really* limiting. Seriously, what options are there for a 65 casual player who plays 5-10 hours a week: for soloing I can go to Droga, Veksar, HoH basement or Char B, for grouping I can do LDON or BoT since those seem to be the only two places casual players ever group anymore. Everything else is too easy, too hard, or nobody groups there.
<br />

<br />
When GoD was released, I was looking forward to some new zones but it turns out you had to have really good gear to hunt in those zones. Quite a few of my friends have defected to City of Heroes. I like EQ, but it's starting to get boring. I had some hope for OOW improving things, but it turns out the "quest" system is only going to be for characters under 50.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
